    "<h3>Safety measures when working on vehicles with auxiliary heating</h3>"
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "warning"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "category" :
    
    
    "Information"
    ,
    
    "consequences" : [
    
    
    
    "It is important to ensure that the auxiliary heating timer is deactivated during a workshop visit and while working on the vehicle in order to prevent the auxiliary heating system from coming on unintentionally."
    ,
    
    
    "The preset timer must be activated again following repair work."
    ,
    
    
    "The auxiliary heating system must not be on or switched on in areas in which there is a danger of fire and risk of explosion."
    ,
    
    
    "The auxiliary heating system must not be on or switched on in enclosed spaces without an exhaust extraction system."
    ,
    
    
    "Always comply with the applicable safety regulations when working on the fuel system."
    ,
    
    
    "The engine must not be started if components of the fuel system (e.g. metering pump, fuel line, fuel supply indicator) are removed or open."
    ,
    
    
    "Before starting repair work on the auxiliary heating system: Relieve overpressure in the cooling system by carefully opening the catch on the coolant reservoir."
    ,
    
    
    "The function of the auxiliary heating system must be checked following repair work on the auxiliary heating system or fuel system."
    ,
    
    
    "When repair work is complete, perform on-board diagnosis of the auxiliary heating system using the vehicle diagnostic tester."
    
    ]
    
